https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-falling-path-sum/description/

QUESTION:
SOLUTION:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME  COMPLEXITY:O(m*n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(m*n)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 1: Create a dp matrix.
Step 2: All the 1st row elements to the dp.
Step 3: if j=0 then you check the min of  [i-1][j] & [i-1][j+1]
Step 4: if j==n-1 then you check the min of[i-1][j] & [i-1][j-1]
Step 5: others you check all three, and find the min. [i-1][j-1] & [i-1][j] & [i-1][j+1]
Step 6: Check the last row which is the min and return that.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public int minFallingPathSum(int[][] matrix) {
        if(matrix==null || matrix.length==0)return 0;
        int min=Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int m=matrix.length;
        int n=matrix[0].length;
        int dp[][]=new int[m][n];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            dp[0][i]=matrix[0][i];
        }
        for(int i=1;i<m;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                if(j==0){
                    dp[i][j]=matrix[i][j]+Math.min(dp[i-1][j],dp[i-1][j+1]);
                }else if(j==n-1){
                    dp[i][j]=matrix[i][j]+Math.min(dp[i-1][j],dp[i-1][j-1]);
                }else{
                    dp[i][j]=matrix[i][j]+Math.min((Math.min(dp[i-1][j-1],dp[i-1][j])),dp[i-1][j+1]);
                }
            }

        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(min>dp[m-1][i]){
                min=dp[m-1][i];
            }
        }
        return min;
    }
}
